The Enduro RX 800 is an all mountain ski that has gobs of technology from the race and freeride scenes. The Salomon RX 800 boasts a full wood core for great flex and durability, while the double monocoque construction lets you put a lot of strain on the edges. Salomon gave this ski their double powerline system for great stability, control, and vibration dampening on bumpy, hard snow. Double titanium reinforcement ensures quick cuts and great traction while turning; you don't have to worryabout those pesky ice patches. While the RX 800 ski is a groomer lover's delight, it is also a great ski for killing those powder days. The Salomon RX 800's all terrain rocker shape gives it a freeski feel on those deep days. Bundled with the oversized Z12 binding, there is no limit to what this thing can handle. The Z12 binding is great for all mountain riding and has extra long wings to increase the boot contact area transferring motion much better than other bindings. This duo is an unstoppable force.
